The paper discusses the implementation of monocular SLAM systems in robotics and augmented reality, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also focuses on keyframe-based solutions, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV) and machine learning algorithms (cs.AI, cs.LG). Additionally, the paper addresses the limitations and future directions of monocular SLAM, which involves system optimization and control (cs.SY).
